  "name": "Capacitor Pulse Circuit",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Capacitor Pulse Circuit",
    "description": "Flip the slide switch on, then off. USB → 470Ω → 100µF capacitor → red LED → ground — the cap is in series, so it blocks steady DC once charged. You get a short flash when the switch changes (charge pulse on, discharge pulse off), not a steady glow like lesson 9. τ ≈ 47 ms with 100µF — much snappier than lesson 19’s 1000µF after the LED. LED at 90° (anode north); cap + toward power."
  },
